Product name: Vintage Mahjongg Set, Crisloid Mah Jongg Set, Vintage Tile Games, Chinese Games, Red Mahjong Set Case, American Mahjong
Description:
Vintage Crisloid Mah Jong set made in the USA. This set contains 164 tiles (including 8 jokers) and instructions. The set is complete with five racks and coins. The back of the tiles are plain, no pattern. No missing tiles.  No damage to any game pieces. Excellent condition.
The case does show some wear on the outside and corrosion on the latches. It is solid and strong however, the latches and hinges work well. The game set inside is in excellent condition, very little use. This Mah Jongg set belonged to my mother. I can't ever remember my mother actually playing it. It's still packed in the original tissue paper, which has yellowed.
The case appears to be covered in red leather cloth and the tiles appear to be bakelite or a similar plastic,  but I can't be 100% sure. This is truly a beautiful collectors set!
The Crisloid company is well known for making high quality board and tile games in the USA and is still in business today.
The case measures 20 x 9 x 3.5 inches and is somewhat heavy. Shipping includes insurance.

Product name: Vintage World Globe WW2 c1945 Regency Styled Illuminated Glass Crams with Bakelite Base
Description:
A 12 inch diameter Illuminated Glass Unrivaled Terrestrial Globe by the George F. Cram Co. Indianapolis, IN
A unique and fine representation of the Hollywood Regency style!  Demanding attention not just with it's elegance and style, this commanding piece is a statuesque 25 inches tall.  When illuminated the globe does not just offer a wonderful, warm, golden ambience, but also shares the history of the lost art of globe production.  Meticulous craftsmanship was needed in the production of this illuminated wonder from the hand blown glass orb to the hand applied and perfectly aligned paper map gores to document the world of 1945.
Glass orbs had only been made for a short period, from the mid 1930s to late 1950's.  Eventually replaced by more economical, mass produced plastic models.  Nothing however can be compared to the patina and warm glow of an illuminated glass terrestrial globe. 
Mounted onto a fabulous brown colored Bakelite base, this model is exceptionally rare, offered only for a brief period of time for commercial use and not offered in the official Cram Co. catalog or sold directly to the general public.  The brass plate with the Art Deco detail could be engraved for any occasion or event.  
The map itself is of upmost interesting details, showing the close of World War 2 before borders are finalized.  The Japanese Manchukuo has regained it's original name (Manchuria) and has been returned to China, Thailand once again has become Siam and will remain so until 1949 when it becomes Thailand again.  The map display Baluchistan which will become Palestine in 1947.
This model is in excellent condition with only a minor lighter colored strip in Africa (this is not missing map but appears to be missing shellac).  The Bakelite base is free of any chips or cracks.  The brass plate has some tarnish or loss of the plating.
An unique and beautiful golden orb on a scarce Bakelite mount!
For International shipping rates please inquire.

Product name: Singer Sewing Machine ED188995 // Vintage cast iron working sewing machine // Hand Crank sewing machine with original case //
Description:
This is a rather stunning vintage singer sewing machine in its original case. The Serial Number is ED 188995 which dates this machine to 1941. It is a heavy cast Iron black machine with a hand crank mechanism. This means that the machine works by turning the handle at the back. 
The artwork on this machine is still really good and not too worn, the gold paint is still vivid and complete. 
The machine mechanism is really smooth, i did a small service but overall it didnt need it, it is working really smoothly. 
Condition: There are some condition notes with this machine: the cover for the accessories box at the back is enamel and the black enamel is flaked off. This can be seen in the pictures.
there are two areas of woodworm also - one at the front of the base and one on the cover. I have treated the whole machine although it looked like it was not an active patch of woodworm. the damage can be seen as a close up in the photos.
The cover fits on perfectly but does not lock so the machine cannot be lifted using the handle on the lid. 
Overall if you want to use this machine it is in really good nick. these machines were built to last! with minor tweaks to the tension gauge it should sew perfectly. It would also be an incredible display piece. 
If you have any questions or would like any additional photos please get in touch and i would be happy to help. 
This weighs 15kgs, hence the cost of shipping.

Product name: Empty Carry Case for Elna Supermatic Sewing Machine- Metal Sewing Machine Case Bed Extender for Elna Supermatics with Foot Pedal, CASE ONLY
Description:
The Swiss-made Elna sewing machines were wonderful little pieces of engineering, and the case was part of the appeal. The cases can be converted into bed extenders so the sewing machine can be used without being installed into a table. This case is for the later Supermatic models. It has a couple of spots on the walls that can be used to hold accessories, including a foot pedal holder. It has a dark gray crinkle paint exterior and a bright bronze interior.
The case is in great shape. It's clean, aside from some flecks of white paint on the outside. There's a small dent in one of the top corners. It opens and closes exactly as it's intended to, and it latches securely. There are a few small patches of rust on the bottom, which I've treated with a rust sealant.
The serial number on the bottom of the case shows that it was made for a 1964 Star Series Elna Supermatic, so it will probably fit best for a machine with a serial number ending in B, but as far as I can tell it should work just fine for any machine with a serial number ending in any of the letters B-L (Production dates 1964-71). It's intended for a machine with a foot pedal, so I can't promise that a free arm sewing machine would fit correctly. Please check your machine against the measurements for this case.
Measures 15" x 12.5" x 7".

Product name: Singer Featherweight, The Classic Portable, Sewing Machine, Quilters Machine, Featherweight 221, Japan Black Finish, Vintage 1952 Singer
Description:
Singer Featherweight, The Classic Portable, Sewing Machine, Quilters Machine, Featherweight 221, Japan Black Finish, Vintage 1952 Singer.
Singer Featherweight 221, the perfect portable. Perfect for taking to quilting classes, perfect for piecing quilts. Such a space saver. I had mine and used it in my tiny apartment in downtown San Francisco. My aunt takes her featherweight with her while traveling in her RV. I knew a teacher who ran a side business making pillows in her tiny apartment, all the sewing was done on her featherweight. The serial number on this wonderful machine indicates a manufacture date of August 11, 1952. This one was made in the Elizabethport, NJ.
This machine is ready to sew!  I had it professionally cleaned, lubed, oiled and adjusted and the belt replaced.   The gold decals are in beautiful shape with no thinning anywhere.  The machine also comes with all the accessories shown in the first picture. It has it's original instruction booklet!  So hard to find these days. The accessories box is in good shape and is original. The foot pedal is original.   It even has the original Singer oil can.  It's a bit banged up but it's the first one I've ever seen.  There's no oil in it and I wouldn't recommend filling it but it's a cool accessory and has it's own metal clip in the case.
The carrying case is original and in very good shape for the 60 years it's been around.  The snap closures work and the hinges and handle are in good working order.  The box itself smells clean and dry.  It looks as though a couple of the top corners were repaired or re-covered a long time ago but the repair works well.   
Shipping for this machine is 75.00 insured to the US only.

Vintage British Sewing Machines Ltd Model 7000, made in the 1930's by Vickers

Product name: Scale model military vehicles artillery gun ISU 152 military gifts USSR panzer soviet military model World War II collectibles Red Army
Description:
Scale model military vehicles artillery gun ISU 152 military gifts USSR panzer soviet military model World War II collectibles Red Army
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Self-propelled artillery unit.
ISU-152 scale model reprinted 1944  1:30
This model was made from the factory construction, made on factory "Twinkle" of the USSR in 1982.
material - polystyrene, rubber tracks
Completeness: no conveyance of the hook back and antenna
The model is not painted.
ISU-152 (Object 241) - Soviet heavy self-propelled artillery unit (SAU) during World War II. In the name of the machine the letter "I" means - "the tank of IP-based." Index of 152 indicates the caliber of the main armament of the machine.
The design of the pilot plant Office number 100 in June - October 1943 and put into service of the Workers 'and Peasants' Red Army (RKKA) November 6, 1943. Then it started mass production at the Chelyabinsk Kirov Plant (CHKZ), which lasted until 1946. Several cars of this stamp issued in 1945 from the Leningrad Kirov Plant (LB). ISU-152 is widely used in the final stages of World War II.
ISU-152 consisted in service with the armies of Poland and Czechoslovakia, the unit captured the car used by the Wehrmacht and the Finnish army.
In the aftermath of the ISU-152 were modernized and long operated by the Soviet army.
 They also delivered to equip the Egyptian armed forces. Sent to Egypt self-propelled guns took part in the Arab-Israeli armed conflict in the Middle East. ISU-152 participated in the Six-Day War in the form of fixed emplacements buried in the sand on the fenders. In Egypt we delivered non-upgraded versions, but they had installed night vision system with infrared illuminator, mounted in pairs with a headlamp in a protective basket on the left of the gun. Since the mid-1970s, the ISU-152 were retired Soviet Army and replaced with more modern automatic control system; a number of survivors from the cutting of metal machines now serve monuments and artifacts in museums around the world.
Slang name ISU-152 - "St. John's Wort." The Wehrmacht it was called «Dosenöffner»

It is large; it measures 52 x 36. The bagging fabric was nearly always 36 inches selvage to selvage. It is better quality than most feed sack fabrics and I was starting to doubt that it was a feed sack until I located the holes where it was stitched.  They are hard to find in this one.
Please see my other listings. I have a number of feed sacks listed. My mother collected them to use in quilting and also collected advertising feed sacks. When I was a child we lived near one of my sets of grandparents. Grandpa was a railroad engineer but he also raised turkeys and chickens. My mom made many items from feedbags--dishtowels, our clothes, her own "house dresses" and used them in quilts, doll clothes and other crafts. The ragged ones became dad's towels in the garage or our cleaning cloths and dust rags. My mom frequently asked my grandpa to try to get 3 bags of the same design so she would have enough to make herself a dress or make kitchen curtains.

Product name: Jürgen Reipka 'Op Art' Serigraph -- signed and numbered
Description:
Jürgen Reipka's (German, 1936-2013) distinctive work is widely collected. This 1960-70s signed and numbered colored silkscreen-like Op-Art composition of his unique style and use of bright colors gives the piece an optical effect of motion. The estimated value of similar works by Reipka ranges from the mid-300s to over 500 in today's market.
The artwork is pencil signed in the lower right ‘Reipka’ and numbered in the lower left (81/100). There are a few small paint losses extending through the image but nothing that detracts from the overall visual and artistic impact of the unframed piece, which you can see in the photos. The outer margins of the sheet have with some wear and there is some paper discoloration around the image (probably from sunlight). The price reflects these issues, however. 
The sheet measures 23.5 x 16.5 inches. and the image is 15 x 14.5 inches. The sheet is embossed at the lower left FR and there is, what looks like a catalogue/inventory number (1--43-81) and a dollar amount of 18 in the center bottom; a bargain originally!
Reipka attended Art School Bremen (1960-63) and from 1963-68 at Art Academy of Fine Arts in Munich (1973) and its president from 1976-79. He was also a Member of the German Association of Artists and the New Group in Munich.

Description:
Cribbage is a fun card game in which players keep score by moving pegs around a track on the board. This full size 121-hole board has tracks for two players, and the hinged lid opens to allow storage for pegs and a standard deck of cards. 
The board is made from solid local Missouri walnut. It comes with six metal pegs for scoring (three silver, three gold, giving you a spare of each); cards not included.

Dimensions: 4 1/2" x 14" x 1 3/8" tall
***Ships in 1-2 weeks.***
If this is a gift and you're having it shipped directly to the recipient, please let us know and we will not include a packing slip/receipt with price info. We'd also be happy to include a gift message. Just include your message in the "note to seller" when you check out.

Product name: DIY "Platinum" ST Style Electric Guitar Kit
Description:
Solid body six string electric guitar kit with beautiful alder body, maple neck, and upgraded locking tuners, bridge and pickups. This is a fantastic quality, easy to build, dual single-coil electric guitar kit.
These kits go together easily, all the parts work together well, and the instrument can be assembled without a lot of experience with woodworking or instrument building.
Every hole is drilled for each component, including neck, bridge, pickguard and strap button mounting holes. No soldering is required; all electronics connect together with easy to attach connectors. We have done most of the hard work for you! The body needs finish sanding only but should require no filling.
The guitar kit comes with chrome hardware, an upgraded tremolo bridge, a white 3-ply pickguard, three single coil pickups, and all necessary hardware. A set of Fender strings is even included.
This is not a cheap Chinese manufactured kit of questionable quality where the parts simply don’t work together (like most of the other kits that you will find on Ebay, Etsy and Amazon). We proudly manufacture these kits in our shop in Portland, Oregon. We are a family-owned company building products and traditions that we expect to last for a long, long time. We produce instrument kits with exacting specifications, high quality production, and domestic, sustainably-cultivated sources of materials whenever possible.
Features:
- Traditional shape and neck profiles
- Wonderful looking solid 2 piece alder body wood. Ready for painting or stains
- Solid Maple neck with Rosewood fret board and dot inlays on face and side of neck
- Awesome fretwork right out of the box
- Bone nut for tone and sustain
- Three traditional single coil pickups
- Upgraded Powered By Lace pickups with staggered Alnico magnets
- 5-way switch, volume and tone control
- Awesome tuning stability with Gotoh SG381-MGT locking tuners with thumbwheel locking mechanism and staggered tuner post height. Very easy to use, very stable tuning!
- Upgraded Wilkinson/Gotoh VSVG Tremolo bridge
- Upgraded electronics, including Orange Drop cap in tone circuit
- 3 Ply White Pickguard
- Every hole is drilled
- No soldering is required: easy snap together connectors (optional pickups are not prewired/soldered)
Technical Specifications:
Body:	Solid Alder, 2 pieces
Shape and Carving:	Traditional shape
Neck Type:	Maple Neck with Rosewood fretboard. Pro-level fret work out of the box
Neck Profile:	Standard 25.5" scale Classic 60's style oval (21.5mm thick at first fret, 43.1mm wide at first fret)
Fretboard Profile:	9.5" Radius
Frets:	22
Fret Gauge:	Medium
Nut:	 Bone nut, slotted and shaped
Nut Width:	42mm
Bridge:	Upgraded tremolo: Wilkinson/Gotoh VSVG
Bridge Mount: Vintage 6 screw mount
String Spacing:	10.8mm
Pickups:	3 x upgraded single coils. Powered by Lace Staggered top, Alnico-V magnets
Controls:	Standard controls. 5 way switch, 1 volume, 2 tone controls
Electronics:	Upgraded, including CTS pots and Orange Drop Capacitor in tone circuit
Wiring:	NO SOLDERING REQUIRED!
Output Jack:	Standard Chrome Output Jack and Plate

Tuning Machines: Gotoh SG381 MG-T High Quality Locking tuning machines Staggered tuner height for further improved tuning stability
Locking Tuners?:	Yes

Tuner hole diameter:	10mm

String Gauges:	010-013-017-026-036-046
Sanding:	Well-sanded. May need touch up sanding only before finishing.
Finish Options:	Beautiful wood, beautiful craftsmanship. Great for natural or sunburst patterns
Assembly process and Instructions:	NO DRILLING REQUIRED! Detailed assembly instructions included
Summary:	The parts for an awesome instrument. You won't be disappointed with the quality. Great pickups, hardware, body and neck/fret work.

Description:

Jose G. Ahumada, owner at Exceptional Craft, has 20 years of experience working in recording/production/live sound/recording studios. 
At  1250.00 dollars, this table is built  out of the highest quality materials to ensure no sagging. 
There is not a single piece made out of compressed wood or MDF. Our tables are 100% solid wood and birch plywood, we have added torsion bars on the piano tray and desktop bottom to ensure no warping down due to gear weight.
The top of this desktop is also strengthened with a 4" depth frame of maple at the front. Maple is a very high quality, hardwood. This addition ensures there will be no warping and sagging throughout the years.
The piano tray is built out of strong birch plywood and has even more added stability due to a iron torsion bar placed at the back of the tray. This is another addition to ensure the piano tray will not sag over many years of use.
The finishes are the highest quality stains and lacquers, applied in multiple layers. 
One of the coolest features about our desks and racks: the Racks are not attached to the desk, they easily slide on the top surface of the desk making it really comfortable to have access to your  gear (moving the racks back and forward) specially in those times when you are tracking a voice and you need quick access to the pre-amp, the guitar POD, Compressor, interface Preamp, etc. also the amount of space left on top of the desk is significantly more than other desks on the market. 
Our goal for each customer is that you never have to worry about your desk again. We have created a product that is a pleasure to use and will look absolutely terrific. 
1250.00 is the price for a desk as seen in the picture. It includes a roll out piano tray and two 4 space racks. 
Customization is available, any color and size  (there might be price adjustment) (some customization might reduce/increase price) send us a message with your  questions.
The Standard piano tray (as shown) is 6 7/8" height by 57 1/2" width. This Piano tray (as shown) fits an 88-weighted keys keyboard, like a motif XS8/XF8.
Desk-top is 65-in wide by 30-in depth. (we can a fit any size keyboard to this piano tray in case you have something like a Rhodes MK80 or kORG 01W PRO FD or any other keyboard! )
The two 4 space rack units included have a depth of 15" giving you plenty of room to place your studio monitors.

Product name: Pop-up Phone Grip in iPhone colours | selfie handgrip stand | Free car mount
Description:
Keep a grip on your Phone with the Pop-Up Phone Grip.
The Pop-Up Phone grip is an innovative Phone accessory which uses an expanding rubber concertina construction to provide a mobile phone grip with three use positions;
 (1)   The flat position allows you to use your phone unhindered by the phone grip as it lies flat against the back of your phone (only a few millimeters thick). 
 (2)   The middle position allows a good grip on your phone while you are calling and a stand with a low viewing angle for watching video.
 (3)   The fully out position gives you a firm grip on the phone for action selfies and video shooting. The fully out position also gives you a stand with a steeper viewing angle.
The phone grip is also an easy and convenient way to store your ear buds, simply leave the buds plugged in and wrap the cord around the Pop-Up grip, pop the grip down and you capture the cable so it can't come loose. You can add one or two grips to your phone depending on your need. Offered in 5 colours, Silver, Rose Gold, White, Black and Space Grey, perfectly matching the iPhone colours.
The Pop-Up Grip can be very useful for larger phones and Tablets which because of their size are not easy to grip (especially with one handed holding and the other on the touch screen
the Pop-Up Phone grip comes with a free car mount making handsfree calling and navigation easy. The car mount can also be used in the house to hold you phone by your charging position, or next to your bed as an easy alarm clock.

Product name: Support téléphone smartphone minimaliste en chêne français. Epuré esthétique type scandinave. iPhone, iPad, Samsung, HTC
Description:
Un beau cadeau pour homme, femme, mamie, papie, enfants, amis et même votre chef. Et pourquoi pas pour vous-même?
Réalisé à la main dans du chêne français issu du développement durable, c'est un objet qui n'a pas de fin de vie. Il est chaleureux, il se marie bien avec le métallique des gadgets, on peut y mettre aussi bien son smartphone que sa tablette (et si on n'a plus on peut l'utiliser comme bougeoir ou support pour un petit pot de fleurs!).
Avant de vous donner les dimensions, regardez un peu la forme. Les angles, la rainure et les trou pour laisser le doigt appuyer sur le buton central. Tout est étudié pour faire un objet unique. Vous pouvez également coucher le téléphone, le support sera tout aussi agréable.
La forme unique lui permet de recevoir même une tablette mini, la surface de la base étant la plus grande possible pour une meilleure stabilité, sans augmenter le poids.
Réalisé sur commande spécialement pour votre téléphone. Avec ou sans protection, avec ou sans coque. A vous de me donner, lors de votre commande, l'épaisseur de votre smartphone (avec ou sans la protection, en fonction de comment vous l'utiliserez sur cet support).
Vient ensemble avec un petit sac en coton (non-traité, Westford Mill ou autre marque équivalente), pour une présentation originale de cadeau. Le téléphone et l'éléphant en bois qui sont présents dans les photos ne sont pas inclus dans le prix.
Eléphant: 
https://www.etsy.com/fr/listing/461294360/decoration-murale-chambre-enfant-jouet
Dimensions approximative base 92 x 73 mm. Epaisseur bois 28 mm.
Poids approx. 150g.
Je livre en France et partout dans le monde, par La Poste. 
Livraison gratuite à Strasbourg, me contacter avant de commander.
Attention: ne laissez pas l'objet dans les mains des petits enfants ou bébés.
Note importante: 
Le bois est un matériau dont les veines ne sont jamais identiques. Donc, le produit que vous allez recevoir peut ne pas être identique aux photos. Le matériau reste le même, les dimensions aussi.
Etant donné que tous mes objets sont réalisés à la main (avec un minimum d'utilisation des machines électriques), ils pourraient avoir des petits défauts de fabrication (petits éclatements dans les coins, rainure non-parfaite, ponçage non-uniforme etc). Ceux-ci ne changent pas l'esthétique de l'objet. Au contraire même, ces petits défauts éventuels lui donnent une âme et rappellent que c'est un humain qui l'a réalisé. Si vous êtes à la recherche d'un objet "IKEA", parfaitement coupé avec une machine numérique sans aucune intervention humaine, vous n'êtes pas sur le bon site.

Product name: Let's dance: illustrated book of poems about dancing
Description:
This is a book for dance-lovers. It’s a book for everyone who catches their breath at the ballet or in front of Strictly Come Dancing, or who can’t look away when someone magnificent takes to the floor in a club. 
Beautifully produced on fine cream paper and with sunflower yellow endpapers, this is a gorgeous collection of new poems by modern poets, assembled by Emma Wright (me!) and Rachel Piercey as a celebration of the joy and magic of dance. There are poems about everything from sloppy kitchen shuffles, strict ballet teachers and underwater waltzes.
The poems are accompanied by 8 line-drawings I've drawn of Northern soul dancers, because I feel I really learned to dance just for myself, without self-consciousness, when I found out about Northern soul a few years ago.
* * *
'The Emma Press Anthology of Dance'
Edited by Rachel Piercey and Emma Wright
ISBN 978-1-910139-15-8 / paperback, perfect bound
80 pages / 42 poems / 8 illustrations / published 9th May 2015
* * *
SOME REVIEWS: 
‘This is a fitting testament to the transformative and empowering potential of dance, an enjoyable anthology, which should appeal to poetry fans and acolytes alike.’ – Jessica Traynor for Sabotage Reviews
‘This is a small, delightful book full of contemporary poems about dance in short, staccato bursts. […] A very enjoyable book that should appeal to both dance fans and poetry lovers with its strong message of the potential of dance to empower and change people’s lives.’ — Lynne Lancaster for Sydney Arts Review
* * *
With poems by Stephanie Arsoska, Sophie F Baker, Dzifa Benson, Jane Burn, John Canfield, George David Clark, Geraldine Clarkson, James Coghill, Brian Docherty, Claire Dyer, Francine Elena, Flora de Falbe, Katherine Gallagher, Hilary Gilmore, Rebecca Goss, Jan Heritage, Sarah Hesketh, Emma-Jane Hughes, Emma Jeremy, Carla Jones, Melinda Kallasmae, Anna Kisby, Gill Learner, Emma Lee, Julie Maclean, Martin Malone, Felicity Maxwell, Paul McMenemy, Margot Myers, Richard O’Brien, Rachel Piercey, Wendy Pratt, Rosie Sandler, Jacqueline Saphra, Catherine Smith, Maria Taylor, Pam Thompson, Andrew Wynn Owen and Lana Faith Young.

THE CANON A-1:
Top model of the A-series Canons - the most advanced and modern SLR in the "A" series 
Has “Program” mode, aperture-priority, shutter priority to freeze or blur motion , and full manual. This combination of shooting modes set the A-1 apart from the other A-series cameras.
Single finger control through a tiny selector wheel on the front of the top plate for shooting in aperture-priority to shutter-priority to Program mode, adjusting the settings in each of these modes, and taking a photo.
A retractable cover protects the selector wheel from accidental movement, and a viewfinder shutter prevents accidental light from spilling onto the film when shooting when not using the viewfinder.
An exceptional selection of slow shutter speeds (2,4,8,15, and 30 sec.) 
Choose your shooting mode, and just shoot. This camera creates exacting exposures in every mode, with every shot. The exposure compensation is there to help things along manually, but most say they've never needed it. 
When shooting in manual mode the camera viewfinder shows the shutter speed and the aperture that it thinks should be used.
Build quality of the A-1 is really good, certainly better than any other A-series camera. The A-1 is stronger, faster, better, than any other A-series machine, and you can feel that fact when you hold and shoot it.
A-1s come with the standard 50mm ƒ/1.8, an extremely capable lens.
This camera is perfect for anyone, from the new student to the highly-advanced photographer. It can do everything any shooter will ask of it.

How to cut a graphic using a Rotary Circle Cutter
1. Place your metal plate on your work surface.
2. Center your graphic on top of the metal plate.
 3. Place the cutter on top of the graphic and center the graphic inside of the center hole.
 4. Hold the cutter firmly with one hand on the edge.
5. Place your other hand on top of the knob and firmly press down.
6. Rotate the knob in a circle around the graphic one or two times while holding the firm pressure.
7. Lift the cutter off the graphic and remove the graphic.
